snippet.textDisplay: Ever since I was a young soldier listening to bootlegged tape in the late 90s with a KATUSA buddy on an all night detail I was hooked on DT. It blasted with me over loud speakers strapped to a HUMVEE in Afghanistan while I manned the .50 cal through hostile territory. They played me through college, studying all night. It was a critical part of my daughter's musical appreciation when I drover her home from school. Working lonely hours enriching uranium, coding late into the night, in my lab now, all the wins and the loses, the good time and f'ed up ones. They've been there. Thank you.
